 When Maps Become the World shows us how the scientific theories, models, and concepts we use to intervene in the world function as maps, and explores the consequences of this, both good and bad. We increasingly understand the world around us in terms of models, to the extent that we often take the models for reality. Winther explains how in time, our historical representations in science, in cartography, and in our stories about ourselves replace individual memories and become dominant social narratives—they become reality, and they can remake the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAbstraction. 0aCartographyxPhilosophy. 0aCartography-Philosophy. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aMental representation. 0aReification. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aanalogy.  acartography.  acreativity.  aenvironmental sciences.  agenetics.  amapping.  aphilosophy of science.  aphysics.  apsychology.  aspace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226674865423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226674865/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deG